class Solution:
    def getTargetCopy(self, original: TreeNode, cloned: TreeNode, target: TreeNode) -> TreeNode:
        # Perform a depth-first search on both trees simultaneously
        def dfs(orig: TreeNode, clone: TreeNode) -> TreeNode:
            if not orig:
                return None
            if orig == target:
                return clone
            # Search in the left subtree
            left_result = dfs(orig.left, clone.left)
            if left_result:
                return left_result
            # Search in the right subtree
            return dfs(orig.right, clone.right)

        return dfs(original, cloned)
```

This solution performs a depth-first search (DFS) on both the original and cloned trees simultaneously. When it finds the target node in the original tree, it returns the corresponding node from the cloned tree. The DFS ensures that we explore each node in the tree, making it suitable for finding the target node and its corresponding copy in the cloned tree.
